{
  "query": "What are the conservation benefits of prohibiting spearfishing in marine reserves in the Mediterranean?",
  "relevant_summary": "Based on the available evidence, prohibiting spearfishing in marine reserves in the Mediterranean provides several conservation benefits for fish populations. Two studies in the Mediterranean Sea (France, Corsica) found that prohibiting spearfishing and line fishing in protected areas increased the abundances of European seabass and gilthead seabream compared to protected and unprotected fished areas after two to seven years (action 2672). The same studies found that European seabass were larger in size in areas where spearfishing was prohibited compared to protected and unprotected fished areas after two to seven years (action 2672). Additionally, one study in the Mediterranean Sea found that prohibiting spearfishing in specific zones of a marine reserve resulted in higher commercial and recreational fishery catches of targeted common dentex compared to zones that allowed spearfishing and areas outside the reserve after one to three years (action 2672). More broadly, studies from the Mediterranean Sea showed that marine protected areas prohibiting all types of fishing for between three and 16 years had different fish community composition compared to fished areas (action 2682). Several Mediterranean studies found that marine protected areas that had prohibited all fishing for between one to more than 25 years had higher fish species richness compared to fished areas (action 2682). Mediterranean studies also found higher abundances and biomasses of all fish, fishery targeted fish species, and individual fish species in marine protected areas that had been prohibiting all fishing for up to 25 years compared to unprotected fished areas (action 2682). Fish in non-fished Mediterranean marine reserves were found to be larger overall and had larger individuals of monitored fish species compared to fished areas after one to 22 years (action 2682). One Mediterranean study found more eggs of four commercially targeted fish species inside a non-fished marine reserve enforced for three years than in fished areas outside the reserve (action 2682).",
  "action_ids": [
    "2672",
    "2682"
  ]
}

